# Documentation

**Devlog (docs/devlogs/v1.txt):** High-level only (what we worked on, not how). No trivial details. All details go in docs/context.txt. One concise summary per day; resummarize in same commit (see commit-and-devlog.mdc).

**Where things live:**
- docs/context.txt — project status, open items, restrictions (not AI behavior rules)
- docs/requirements.md — features → use cases with checkboxes; [DRAFT] items also in context "Open Conversations"
- docs/frontend-tree.md — source of truth for src/ atoms, layouts, pages
- docs/design.md — colour palette; use with hierarchy
- docs/architecture/ — diagrams for components, auth, routing; update when adding/changing major structure

**Update in same commit when changing:** frontend structure → frontend-tree.md; context/shell/routing → docs/architecture/.

**Formats:** requirements = tree with checkboxes; devlog = daily "What We Accomplished" / "What's Unfinished"; context = sections Open Conversations, Restrictions, Requirements, Bugs. Explain what code does before committing.
